Installing the tftp server


# 6/20/2024
- Ensure you shut off all SElinux
    - https://tecadmin.net/how-to-disable-selinux-on-fedora/
    - https://www.linuxquestions.org/questions/linux-networking-3/tftp-permission-denied-557578/

# dnf install tftp-server

    Start and enable the tftp socket. systemd will automatically start the tftpd service when required.

# systemctl start tftp.socket
# systemctl enable tftp.socket


FirewallD
- https://orcacore.com/manage-firewalld-fedora39-terminal/

